result.execSummary:
Carrieanne Christen Borlek was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Carrieanne Christen Borlek was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 10:30 a.m.  Defendant Carrieanne Christen Borlek in court, in custody.  Martin J. Lipske appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  DA calls case.  Extradition case.  Complaint served on def.  PDef info given to def.  Copy of waiver and consent form provided to def.  Court explains rights to attorney and hearing.  Court questions def re extradition.  Defendant agrees to waive extradition.  Understands will be sent to MI.  Copy of waiver and consent signed by def.  Court witnesses def signing document, is reviewing doc, approves and signs document.  Adjourned at 10:33 a.m.  klr
